{@--1@} To get
up, stand, rise, raise oneself;  
{#uttizWetpraTamaM cAsya#} <ls>Ms. 2. 194</ls>; <ls>R. 9. 59</ls>;
<ls>Śi. 9. 39.</ls>

{@--2@} To get up from, leave,
give up or cease from;  
{#anaSanAduttizWati#} <ls>Pt. 4.</ls>

{@--5@} To come forth, arise, spring
or originate from, accrue from; {#grA#}
{#mAcCatamuttizWati#} Mbh; {#yaduttizWati#} 
{#varReByo nfpARa kzayitatPalaM#} <ls>Ś. 2. 13</ls>;  
{#anyadamftAdutTitam#} <ls>K. 136</ls>; {#udatizWan praSaMsAvAcaH#}
<ls>Dk. 49</ls> shouts of applause burst forth
(were heard); <ls>N. 22. 44.</ls>

{@--7@}
To become animated, rise (from
the dead); {#mftetTitA#} <ls>Ku. 7. 4.</ls>

{@--8@}
To be active or brave, rise up;
{#hfdayadOrbalyaM tyaktvottizWa#} <ls>Bg. 2. 3</ls>, <ls n="Bg. 2.">37</ls>;
<ls>Mv. 2</ls>; <ls>Pt. 3. 21.</ls>

{@--9@} To make
efforts; take pains, strive, try;  
{#uttizWamAnaM mitrArTe kastvAM na bahu manyate#}  
<ls>Bk. 8. 12</ls>; <ls n="Bk.">20. 18</ls>; <ls>Mv. 4. 6</ls>;  
{#mukAvuttizWate janaH#} <ls>Ki. 11. 13</ls>; {#udasTita kratO#}  
<ls>Śi. 14. 17.</ls>

{@--2@} To
instigate, excite, rouse to action;
{#tvAmutTApayati dvayaM#} <ls>Śi. 2. 57</ls>, <ls n="Śi. 2.">102</ls>;
<ls>Kām. 5. 40</ls>; <ls>H. 3. 92</ls>; <ls>Dk. 107.</ls>

{@--3@} To arouse, awaken, raise to
life, make alive; {#prARo hIdaM#} 
{#sarvamutTApayati#} <ls>Śat. Br.</ls>

{@--4@} To support, feed,
aid; {#atra parikarotTApito'#} 
{#rTAMtaranyAsAlaMkAraH#} <ls>Malli.</ls> on <ls>Ki. 8. 4.</ls>
